metadata.name: Eagles in the Stars
metadata.description:
The Eagle Nebula is a spectacular column of gas and dust raising from a region in the Constellation of Serpens where new stars are born. In this artwork, a tree on Earth represents, similarly, a new life. The kaleidoscope symmetry reminds a Rorschach projection which adds a surprise effect that leaves space to individual interpretations. 

Science facts: new stars are born in clouds of cold hydrogen. In such dynamics clouds of dust and gas are pushed away and form the pillars. A band of massime, hot, young stars (off the top of the image) emits the ultraviolet light we can see at the top of the pillars. 

The artwork includes a reinterpretation of the image of the Eagle Nebula as pictured by ESA/Hubble. 

Original Artwork by @federicart
2048x2048 pixels
